Combo is the warrior-style chained attack system.

As you land combo-tagged skills (like punch, kick, knee, headbutt, bash,
charge, and some finishers), your combo track fills. Repeating the same
skill in one sequence breaks the chain.

Combo size (max chain slots) is class-tiered:
- Base Warrior (or 20+ Warrior reincarnations): 4 max combo
- +1 if Crusader adept path is active (or equivalent adept reincarnation tier)
- +1 if Knight or Swordsman remort path is active (or equivalent remort tier)
So practical finisher tiers are usually 4 / 5 / 6 max combo.

Finisher-ready happens at one slot before max (max-1):
- 4 max combo -> finisher-ready at 3
- 5 max combo -> finisher-ready at 4
- 6 max combo -> finisher-ready at 5

When finisher-ready, you can use actions such as fleche, holystrike, riposte,
shieldblock, or anti-magic shell (if your class can use them).

If your combo reaches full readiness, the combo system can trigger extra
follow-up attacks based on the skills in your chain.
